# Card Dispute Portal API

A RESTful API for managing card transaction disputes built with ASP.NET Core and Entity Framework Core.

## Prerequisites

- .NET 10.0 SDK (for local development)
- Docker & Docker Compose (for containerized deployment)

## Project Structure
```
CardDisputeAPI/
├── CardDisputeAPI/                    # API layer (Controllers, Program.cs)
├── CardDisputePortal.Core/            # Domain layer (Entities, DTOs, Interfaces)
├── CardDisputePortal.Infrastructure/  # Data layer (DbContext, Services)
└── CardDisputeAPI.Tests/              # Unit tests
```

## Docker Deployment (Recommended)

### 1. Clone Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Junior-moraba/CardDisputeAPI.git
cd CardDisputeAPI
```

### 2. Build and Run with Docker Compose
```bash
docker-compose up -d --build
```

This automatically:
- Builds the API container
- Starts SQL Server container
- Creates the database and applies migrations
- Seeds test data

### 3. Access the API
- API: http://localhost:7231
- Swagger UI: http://localhost:7231/swagger
- SQL Server: localhost:1433 (sa/YourStrong@Passw0rd)

### 4. View Logs
```bash
docker-compose logs -f api
```

### 5. Stop Containers
```bash
docker-compose down
```

## Test User

The application includes a predefined test user:
- **Phone Number**: `0648952191`
- **Name**: Junior Moraba
- Includes 15 sample transactions with 3 disputes

Use this phone number to test authentication and dispute functionality.

## Local Development

### 1. Restore Dependencies
```bash
dotnet restore
```

### 2. Update Database
```bash
cd CardDisputeAPI
dotnet ef database update
cd ..
```

### 3. Run the API
```bash
dotnet run --project CardDisputeAPI/CardDisputePortal.API.csproj
```

API will be available at: https://localhost:7000 or http://localhost:5000

## Running Tests
```bash
# Run all tests
dotnet test

# Run with detailed output
dotnet test --verbosity normal

# Run specific test class
dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~AuthServiceTests"
```

## Technology Stack
- ASP.NET Core 10.0
- Entity Framework Core 10.0
- SQL Server
- JWT Authentication
- xUnit for testing
- Docker

## Notes
- OTP codes are returned in the response for testing purposes (Only for testing purposes)
- JWT tokens expire after 5 minutes
- Refresh tokens are stored in-memory
- CORS is configured for localhost:5173 and localhost:4173
- Database is automatically created and seeded on first run